## React Hook Form Resolvers

<a href="#react-hook-form-resolvers" id="user-content-react-hook-form-resolvers" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: React Hook Form Resolvers"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

</div>

This function allows you to use any external validation library such as Yup, Zod, Joi, Vest, Ajv and many others. The goal is to make sure you can seamlessly integrate whichever validation library you prefer. If you're not using a library, you can always write your own logic to validate your forms.

<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto">

<a href="#install" id="user-content-install" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Install"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

## TypeScript

<a href="#typescript" id="user-content-typescript" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: TypeScript"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

</div>

Most of the resolvers can infer the output type from the schema. See comparison table for more details.

<div class="highlight highlight-source-tsx notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" snippet-clipboard-copy-content="useForm&lt;Input, Context, Output&gt;()">

    useForm<Input, Context, Output>()

</div>

Example:

<div class="highlight highlight-source-tsx notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" snippet-clipboard-copy-content="import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import { z } from 'zod'; // or 'zod/v4'

const schema = z.object({
  id: z.number(),
});

// Automatically infers the output type from the schema
useForm({
  resolver: zodResolver(schema),
});

// Force the output type
useForm&lt;z.input&lt;typeof schema&gt;, any, z.output&lt;typeof schema&gt;&gt;({
  resolver: zodResolver(schema),
});">

    import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
    import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
    import { z } from 'zod'; // or 'zod/v4'

    const schema = z.object({
      id: z.number(),
    });

    // Automatically infers the output type from the schema
    useForm({
      resolver: zodResolver(schema),
    });

    // Force the output type
    useForm<z.input<typeof schema>, any, z.output<typeof schema>>({
      resolver: zodResolver(schema),
    });

</div>

## API

<a href="#api" id="user-content-api" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: API"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

</div>

<div class="snippet-clipboard-content notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" snippet-clipboard-copy-content="type Options = {
  mode: 'async' | 'sync',
  raw?: boolean
}

resolver(schema: object, schemaOptions?: object, resolverOptions: Options)">

``` notranslate
type Options = {
  mode: 'async' | 'sync',
  raw?: boolean
}

resolver(schema: object, schemaOptions?: object, resolverOptions: Options)
```

</div>

|                 | type     | Required | Description                                   |
|-----------------|----------|----------|-----------------------------------------------|
| schema          | `object` | ✓        | validation schema                             |
| schemaOptions   | `object` |          | validation library schema options             |
| resolverOptions | `object` |          | resolver options, `async` is the default mode |

## Quickstart

<a href="#quickstart" id="user-content-quickstart" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Quickstart"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

      &lt;input {...register('password')} /&gt;
      {errors.password &amp;&amp; &lt;span role=&quot;alert&quot;&gt;{errors.password.message}&lt;/span&gt;}
      &lt;button type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;submit&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/form&gt;
  );
};">

    import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
    import { vineResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/vine';
    import vine from '@vinejs/vine';

    const schema = vine.compile(
      vine.object({
        username: vine.string().minLength(1),
        password: vine.string().minLength(1),
      }),
    );

    const App = () => {
      const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm({
        resolver: vineResolver(schema),
      });

      return (
        <form onSubmit={handleSubmit((d) => console.log(d))}>
          <input {...register('username')} />
          {errors.username && <span role="alert">{errors.username.message}</span>}
          <input {...register('password')} />
          {errors.password && <span role="alert">{errors.password.message}</span>}
          <button type="submit">submit</button>
        </form>
      );
    };

### [fluentvalidation-ts](https://github.com/AlexJPotter/fluentvalidation-ts)

<a href="#fluentvalidation-ts" id="user-content-fluentvalidation-ts" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: fluentvalidation-ts"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

A TypeScript-first library for building strongly-typed validation rules

<a href="https://bundlephobia.com/result?p=@vinejs/vine" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/b2a100f57f8ee99a43563f103cef0da5899423a2a528dd8abd685fe596dd75db/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62756e646c6570686f6269612f6d696e7a69702f4076696e656a732f76696e653f7374796c653d666f722d7468652d6261646765" style="max-width: 100%;" data-canonical-src="https://img.shields.io/bundlephobia/minzip/@vinejs/vine?style=for-the-badge" alt="npm" /></a>

<div class="highlight highlight-source-ts notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" snippet-clipboard-copy-content="import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { fluentValidationResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/fluentvalidation-ts';
import { Validator } from 'fluentvalidation-ts';

class FormDataValidator extends Validator&lt;FormData&gt; {
  constructor() {
    super();

    this.ruleFor('username')
      .notEmpty()
      .withMessage('username is a required field');
    this.ruleFor('password')
      .notEmpty()
      .withMessage('password is a required field');
  }
}

const App = () =&gt; {
  const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm({
    resolver: fluentValidationResolver(new FormDataValidator()),
  });

  return (
    &lt;form onSubmit={handleSubmit((d) =&gt; console.log(d))}&gt;
      &lt;input {...register('username')} /&gt;
      {errors.username &amp;&amp; &lt;span role=&quot;alert&quot;&gt;{errors.username.message}&lt;/span&gt;}
      &lt;input {...register('password')} /&gt;
      {errors.password &amp;&amp; &lt;span role=&quot;alert&quot;&gt;{errors.password.message}&lt;/span&gt;}
      &lt;button type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;submit&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/form&gt;
  );
};">

    import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
    import { fluentValidationResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/fluentvalidation-ts';
    import { Validator } from 'fluentvalidation-ts';

    class FormDataValidator extends Validator<FormData> {
      constructor() {
        super();

        this.ruleFor('username')
          .notEmpty()
          .withMessage('username is a required field');
        this.ruleFor('password')
          .notEmpty()
          .withMessage('password is a required field');
      }
    }

    const App = () => {
      const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm({
        resolver: fluentValidationResolver(new FormDataValidator()),

      return (

          <input {...register('username')} />
          {errors.username && <span role="alert">{errors.username.message}</span>}
          <input {...register('password')} />
          {errors.password && <span role="alert">{errors.password.message}</span>}
          <button type="submit">submit</button>
        </form>
      );
    };

      {errors.age?.message &amp;&amp; &lt;p&gt;{errors.age?.message}&lt;/p&gt;}

    &lt;/form&gt;
  );
};">

    import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
    import { standardSchemaResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/standard-schema';

    const schema = z.object({
      name: z.string().min(1, { message: 'Required' }),

    const App = () => {

        register,
        handleSubmit,
        formState: { errors },
